Good. If the Constitution defines what may never drift, then the Compiler defines how Pantheon grows without becoming a junk drawer.

This is where I think Pantheon can become fundamentally different from most knowledge repositories. Most systems only store ideas. A compiler transforms, validates, compresses, and integrates them before they become canonical.

