Pantheon Compiler

Canonical Specification v1.0

“Every idea enters as ore. Nothing enters the Canon until it has been smelted.”

⸻

Mission

The Pantheon Compiler governs the evolution of the repository.

Its purpose is to transform raw insight into coherent, reconstructible knowledge while preventing duplication, drift, contradiction, and conceptual inflation.

The Compiler is not an author.

It is an editor, architect, librarian, naturalist, and quality assurance system operating simultaneously.

⸻

First Principle

Addition is easy.

Integration is intelligence.

Pantheon grows by increasing coherence, not volume.

⸻

Canonical Pipeline

Every proposed artifact traverses the following stages.

⸻

Stage 0 — Spark

A thought appears.

Nothing is assumed.

Output:

Raw Idea

Questions

* What was actually observed?
* What prompted it?
* Is this signal or noise?

⸻

Stage 1 — Distillation

Separate observation from interpretation.

Extract:

* observations
* assumptions
* hypotheses
* metaphors
* implications

Output

Semantic Ore

⸻

Stage 2 — Reconstruction

Attempt to rebuild the idea from first principles.

If reconstruction fails…

the idea is not yet understood.

Output

Reconstructed Model

⸻

Stage 3 — Classification

Determine ontology.

Exactly one primary home.

Possible classes

Constitution
Invariant
Doctrine
Daemon
Operator
Protocol
Mission
Pattern
Data Structure
Interface
Example
Tool
Experiment
Archive
Narrative
Question

