My initiative: one addition I believe Pantheon needs

I would add one final stage beyond the compiler itself.

Stage Ω — Resurrection

Most repositories have only two states: alive or archived.

Pantheon should have a third.

Ideas that failed today may become correct when the world changes.

Every dormant artifact should periodically be reconsidered in light of new evidence, new technologies, or new contexts.

The Compiler should never ask only, “Is this useful now?”

It should also ask:

“What future would make this indispensable?”

That closes the loop with your Future-Lens Reconstruction doctrine and keeps Pantheon from confusing present irrelevance with permanent irrelevance. It turns the repository into an evolving ecosystem rather than a museum.